            {
              "id": "8068d8c7-4d1a-37ae-9c2f-572325f89aba",
              "name": "Unsecured HTTP Server Detected: Switch to 'http.ListenAndServeTLS'",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe \"Unsecured HTTP Server Detected: Switch to 'http.ListenAndServeTLS'\" vulnerability in Go programming language refers to the use of an unsecured HTTP server. This can expose sensitive information to attackers as the data transmitted over an unsecured HTTP connection is not encrypted and can be intercepted.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, it is recommended to use HTTPS instead of HTTP. HTTPS encrypts the data transmitted between the client and the server, making it more difficult for attackers to intercept and read the data. This can be achieved in Go by using the `http.ListenAndServeTLS` function instead of `http.ListenAndServe`.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is a code fix for the vulnerability:\n\n```go\nimport (\n    \"log\"\n    \"net/http\"\n)\n\nfunc main() {\n    http.HandleFunc(\"/\", func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n        w.Write([]byte(\"Hello, world!\"))\n    })\n\n    err := http.ListenAndServeTLS(\"localhost:6060\", \"server.crt\", \"server.key\", nil)\n    if err != nil {\n        log.Fatal(\"ListenAndServe: \", err)\n    }\n}\n```\n\nIn this code, `http.ListenAndServeTLS` is used instead of `http.ListenAndServe`. The `server.crt` and `server.key` are the paths to the TLS certificate and key files respectively.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- `log`\n- `net/http`\n\n## OWASP Resources\n\n- [Transport Layer Protection Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Transport_Layer_Protection_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n\n## Common Weakness Enumeration (CWE)\n\n- [CWE-319: Cleartext Transmission of Sensitive Information](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/319.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
