            {
              "id": "23b3d724-4804-3c82-b770-cc5a5977ff84",
              "name": "Potential for nil dereference panic due to modification of `getClusterOptionsResp` variable.",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe vulnerability is a potential nil dereference panic in Go programming language. It occurs when the `getClusterOptionsResp` variable is modified. If the `GetClusterOptions` function call fails, it may return a nil `getClusterOptionsResp` and a non-nil error. In such a case, the subsequent access to `getClusterOptionsResp.RawResponse` could cause a nil dereference panic, crashing the program.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this issue, you should always check if the returned pointer is not nil before accessing its fields. This can be done by adding an additional nil check for `getClusterOptionsResp` before accessing `getClusterOptionsResp.RawResponse`.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is the recommended fix for the code:\n\n```go\ngetClusterOptionsResp, err := containerClient.GetClusterOptions(context.Background(), getClusterOptionsReq)\nif err != nil {\n\thttpErr := httperror.ErrorCode{}\n\tif getClusterOptionsResp != nil && getClusterOptionsResp.RawResponse != nil {\n\t\thttpErr.Status = getClusterOptionsResp.RawResponse.StatusCode\n\t} else {\n\t\thttpErr.Status = httperror.ServerError.Status\n\t}\n\tlogrus.Debugf(\"[oci-handler] error getting cluster options with ContainerEngine client: %v\", err)\n\treturn nil, httpErr.Status, err\n}\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- `context`: Standard library package for context management in Go.\n- `httperror`: Custom package for handling HTTP errors.\n- `logrus`: Third-party package for logging in Go.\n- `containerClient`: Custom package for interacting with a container engine.\n\n## OWASP and CWE Links\n\n- [CWE-476: NULL Pointer Dereference](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/476.html)"
