            {
              "id": "d480b9ac-2058-3b69-8df8-eb11530d9c1d",
              "name": "Potential Nil Dereference Vulnerability in `availabilityDomains` Variable Modification",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe code snippet provided is vulnerable to a potential nil dereference vulnerability. This occurs when the `availabilityDomains` variable is nil and the program tries to access its `RawResponse` field. This can happen if the `ListAvailabilityDomains` function call fails and returns an error, causing `availabilityDomains` to be nil.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, you should always check if a variable is nil before trying to access its fields or methods. This is especially important when dealing with return values from functions that can fail and return nil values.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is a recommended fix for the code snippet:\n\n```go\navailabilityDomains, err := identityClient.ListAvailabilityDomains(context.Background(), request)\nif err != nil {\n    if availabilityDomains != nil {\n        logrus.Debugf(\"[oci-handler] error listing ADs with Identity client: %v\", err)\n        return nil, getErrorCode(availabilityDomains.RawResponse), err\n    } else {\n        logrus.Debugf(\"[oci-handler] error listing ADs with Identity client: %v\", err)\n        return nil, nil, err\n    }\n}\n```\n\nIn this fix, we first check if `availabilityDomains` is not nil before trying to access its `RawResponse` field.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code snippet provided requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- `context`: Standard library package for managing context.\n- `logrus`: Third-party library for logging.\n- `identityClient`: Custom library for managing identity.\n\n## OWASP and CWE Links\n\n- [CWE-476: NULL Pointer Dereference](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/476.html)"
