            {
              "id": "f8f5efeb-9bf4-3e44-bb3c-f4e2180765f1",
              "name": "Potential for nil dereference panic due to modification of `errcode` variable.",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe code snippet provided is vulnerable to a nil dereference panic. This can occur if the `errcode` variable is `nil` when the error handling block is executed. In Go, trying to access a field or method of a `nil` value will cause a runtime panic, which can crash the application.\n\nIn this specific case, if `v.getCloudCredential(id, req)` returns an error and `errcode` is `nil`, the application will panic when trying to access `errcode.Status` and `errcode.Code`.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, you should always check if a variable is `nil` before trying to access its fields or methods. This is especially important when dealing with error handling, as errors often indicate unexpected situations where some values may be `nil`.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is a recommended fix for the code snippet:\n\n```go\ncc, errcode, err = v.getCloudCredential(id, req)\nif err != nil {\n    if errcode != nil {\n        util.ReturnHTTPError(res, req, errcode.Status, fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %s\", errcode.Code, err.Error()))\n    } else {\n        util.ReturnHTTPError(res, req, http.StatusInternalServerError, err.Error())\n    }\n    return\n}\n```\n\nIn this fixed version, we first check if `errcode` is `nil` before trying to access its fields. If `errcode` is `nil`, we return a generic internal server error.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code snippet seems to depend on the following libraries:\n\n- A library that provides the `v.getCloudCredential(id, req)` method. The specific library cannot be determined from the snippet.\n- The `net/http` standard library for the `http.StatusInternalServerError` constant.\n- A utility library that provides the `util.ReturnHTTPError(res, req, status, message)` function. The specific library cannot be determined from the snippet.\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP Top 10 - A1 Injection](https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/2017/A1_2017-Injection)\n- [CWE-476: NULL Pointer Dereference](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/476.html)"
