            {
              "id": "3ddc1ed8-4f86-3156-9b10-7dcfcd105563",
              "name": "Direct Writing Detected in 'http.ResponseWriter.write()', Bypassing HTML Escaping and Increasing Cross-Site Scripting Vulnerabilities",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nIn Go programming language, the `http.ResponseWriter.write()` function is used to write data to the HTTP response. If user-controlled data is directly written to the HTTP response without proper sanitization or encoding, it can lead to Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) vulnerabilities. XSS vulnerabilities occur when an attacker is able to inject malicious scripts into web pages viewed by other users. These scripts can steal sensitive information, perform actions on behalf of the user, or exploit other vulnerabilities in the user's browser.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, it is recommended to always sanitize and encode user-controlled data before writing it to the HTTP response. This can be done using the `html/template` package in Go, which automatically encodes data when rendering HTML templates.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nInstead of directly writing user-controlled data to the HTTP response, use the `html/template` package to render an HTML template with the user-controlled data:\n\n```go\nimport \"html/template\"\n\n// ...\n\nt, err := template.New(\"userOrgs\").Parse(\"<div>{{.}}</div>\")\nif err != nil {\n    // handle error\n}\n\nerr = t.Execute(w, userOrgs)\nif err != nil {\n    // handle error\n}\n```\n\nIn this example, `{{.}}` is a placeholder for the user-controlled data. The `html/template` package automatically encodes the data, preventing XSS vulnerabilities.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- The `html/template` package, which is part of the standard library in Go.\n\n## OWASP Resources\n\n- [OWASP Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)](https://owasp.org/www-community/attacks/xss/)\n\n## Common Weakness Enumeration (CWE)\n\n- [CWE-79: Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-79",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html"
                  }
                ],
                "severity": "MEDIUM",
                "kind": "FAIL",
