            {
              "id": "9e165416-8171-3538-8d7d-da22933fcba9",
              "name": "User-Input Crafted HTTP Redirect Vulnerability Detected",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\n\"User-Input Crafted HTTP Redirect Vulnerability Detected\" is a security vulnerability that occurs when an application accepts user-controlled input that specifies a link to an external site, and uses that link in a Redirect call. This could allow an attacker to craft a malicious URL that redirects users to a malicious site that performs phishing attacks, exposes the user to malicious content, or performs other malicious actions.\n\nThis vulnerability is also known as \"Unvalidated Redirects and Forwards\" and is listed in the OWASP Top 10.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, you should avoid using user input to determine the destination of redirects without validation. If it's necessary to redirect to a URL provided by the user, ensure that the supplied value is valid, safe, and intended. This can be done by maintaining a list of authorized URLs to which you can redirect and by validating user-supplied URLs against this list.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is a simple way to validate the URL against a list of authorized URLs:\n\n```go\nauthorizedUrls := map[string]bool{\n    \"http://example.com\": true,\n    \"http://example2.com\": true,\n    // add more authorized URLs here\n}\n\nredirectURL, err := url.ParseRequestURI(urlString)\nif err != nil {\n    log.Fatal(err)\n}\n\nif _, ok := authorizedUrls[redirectURL.String()]; ok {\n    http.Redirect(w, r, redirectURL.String(), http.StatusFound)\n} else {\n    log.Println(\"Unauthorized redirect to\", redirectURL.String())\n    // handle unauthorized URL\n}\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example requires the following libraries:\n\n- `net/http`: for the `http.Redirect` function and `http.ResponseWriter` and `http.Request` types.\n- `net/url`: for the `url.ParseRequestURI` function.\n- `log`: for logging errors and unauthorized redirects.\n\n## References\n\n- [CWE-601: URL Redirection to Untrusted Site ('Open Redirect')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/601.html)"
              },
