            {
              "id": "f2729e6b-1ab7-329c-b62f-593ff1e2060d",
              "name": "Unsecured Session Cookie Detected",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe \"Unsecured Session Cookie Detected\" vulnerability refers to the situation where a web application does not properly secure its session cookies. This can lead to potential attacks such as session hijacking, where an attacker can steal the session cookie and impersonate the user.\n\nIn the provided Go code, a cookie is being set without the `Secure` and `HttpOnly` flags. The `Secure` flag ensures that the cookie is only sent over HTTPS, preventing it from being intercepted in plaintext over an unencrypted HTTP connection. The `HttpOnly` flag prevents the cookie from being accessed through client-side scripts, mitigating the risk of cross-site scripting (XSS) attacks.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, you should always set the `Secure` and `HttpOnly` flags for cookies that contain sensitive information such as session identifiers. This ensures that the cookies are only sent over secure connections and cannot be accessed via client-side scripting.\n\n## Source Code Fix\n\nHere is how you can modify the provided Go code to set the `Secure` and `HttpOnly` flags:\n\n```go\nr.AddCookie(&http.Cookie{\n    Name:     \"R_OIDC_ID\",\n    Value:    \"test-id-token\",\n    Secure:   true,\n    HttpOnly: true,\n})\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe provided code snippet does not appear to have any external library dependencies beyond the standard Go library.\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP - SecureFlag](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Session_Management_Cheat_Sheet.html#secure-attribute)\n- [OWASP - HttpOnly](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Session_Management_Cheat_Sheet.html#httponly-attribute)\n- [CWE-614: Sensitive Cookie in HTTPS Session Without 'Secure' Attribute](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/614.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-614",
