            {
              "id": "6d3e8459-9016-378b-ae34-db3dd8a427b3",
              "name": "Potential Nil Dereference Vulnerability in `group` Variable Modification",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe code snippet provided is vulnerable to a potential nil dereference vulnerability in the `group` variable modification. This vulnerability occurs when the `group` variable is `nil` and the program tries to access its `Name` property. If `group` is `nil`, the program will panic and crash, leading to a denial of service.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, you should always check if a variable is `nil` before trying to access its properties or methods. This can be done by adding an additional condition in the `if` statement to check if `group` is `nil`.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is a recommended fix for the code:\n\n```go\ngroup, err = s.groups.Update(group)\nif err != nil || group == nil {\n    if group == nil {\n        logrus.Error(\"scim::PatchGroup: group is nil\")\n    } else {\n        logrus.Errorf(\"scim::PatchGroup: failed to update group: %s\", err)\n    }\n    writeError(w, NewInternalError())\n    return\n}\n```\n\nIn this fix, we added a check for `group == nil` in the `if` statement. If `group` is `nil`, we log an error message and return.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code snippet provided requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- The `logrus` package for logging errors.\n- The `s.groups.Update` method, which is likely part of a custom package.\n\n## OWASP and CWE Links\n\n- [CWE-476: NULL Pointer Dereference](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/476.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-476",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/476.html"
                  }
                ],
                "severity": "MEDIUM",
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "tags": [
                  "CWE-476"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "d43df6df-0e21-3f19-aac5-6fd5ce07a90d",
              "name": "Potential for Nil Dereference Panic due to Modification of `group` Variable",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe code snippet provided is vulnerable to a potential nil dereference panic in Go programming language. This can occur when the `group` variable is modified and then dereferenced without a prior nil check. If `group` is nil, the program will panic when trying to access `group.Name`, leading to a crash.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, it is recommended to always check if a pointer is nil before dereferencing it. This can be done by adding an if statement to check if `group` is nil before trying to access `group.Name`.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is a recommended fix for the code:\n\n```go\ngroup, err = s.groups.Update(group)\nif err != nil {\n    if group != nil {\n        return nil, false, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to update group %s: %w\", group.Name, err)\n    } else {\n        return nil, false, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to update group: %w\", err)\n    }\n}\n```\n\nIn this fix, we first check if `group` is not nil before trying to access `group.Name`. If `group` is nil, we return an error message without trying to access `group.Name`.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code snippet does not provide enough context to determine the exact library dependencies. However, it seems to be using a custom `groups` package for group management and the built-in `fmt` package for formatting error messages.\n\n## OWASP and CWE Links\n\n- [CWE-476: NULL Pointer Dereference](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/476.html)\n\nPlease note that these links are subject to change and may not be accessible at a later date."
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-476",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/476.html"
                  }
                ],
                "severity": "MEDIUM",
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "tags": [
